article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 47, Savannah St. 42
article.story: strdf DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Four Bethune-Cookman players hit eight out of ten free throws in the final 30 seconds of their game against Savannah State to win 47-42 Wednesday night. The top scorer for Bethune-Cookman (8-18) was Dewayne Pettus with nine points. John Anderson and Ron Mitchell contributed another eight points each. Joshua Obiajunwa put up 11 points for Savannah State (11-18), and Javon Randolph added ten. Bethune-Cookman never trailed in the first half, taking a 17-16 lead into the break. Savannah State, with five points from Patrick Hardy, moved to a four-point lead, 25-21, with 15:21 left in the second half. A 10-0 run for Bethune-Cookman put the team back in charge by seven, 35-28. But Savannah State fought back late behind Lazarius Coleman's five straight points to get within two, 44-42.
